        <h3>Houzz Pro — Best for smaller custom builders and design-build</h3>
        <p>Houzz Pro is an excellent fit for smaller custom builders doing 5–15 homes per year, particularly those who also handle interior design elements or work in design-build. The Houzz platform's visual nature aligns with clients who are heavily invested in the aesthetic outcome of their home — and the lead generation helps smaller builders find new clients.</p>

        <div class="cta-box">
          <p><strong>Smaller custom builders and design-build homebuilders: Houzz Pro is worth a look.</strong></p>
          <a href="https://www.houzz.com/pro" rel="nofollow sponsored" class="btn">Try Houzz Pro Free</a>
        </div>

        <h3>CoConstruct — Purpose-built for custom builders</h3>
        <p>CoConstruct (now integrated with Buildertrend after their merger) was long considered the other top option for custom homebuilders. The CoConstruct platform features have been merged into Buildertrend's platform, making Buildertrend even stronger for the custom builder use case.</p>

        <h3>JobTread — For builders who prioritize job costing</h3>
        <p>Custom builders who want precise job costing — and who find Buildertrend's pricing a stretch — should evaluate JobTread. Its job costing is excellent, and for builders doing 10–20 custom homes per year, it covers the essential financial visibility needs.</p>

